🔐 OWASP Top 10 – Learning Log (TryHackMe)
📌 Overview

This repository documents my learning progress through a TryHackMe room covering selected topics from the OWASP Top 10 (2021/2025). The focus was on understanding common web application vulnerabilities, their impact, and basic mitigation strategies.

📚 Covered Topics
A04: Cryptographic Failures
Weak or improper encryption
Sensitive data exposure
Secure data handling practices
A05: Injection
SQL Injection, Command Injection
Root causes and exploitation basics
Input validation and sanitization
A08: Software and Data Integrity Failures
Integrity verification issues
Insecure CI/CD pipelines
Dependency and update risks

🎯 Learning Outcomes
Gained practical understanding of critical web vulnerabilities
Learned how common misconfigurations lead to exploitation
Strengthened secure coding and defensive mindset
Improved ability to identify and analyze security flaws


